steps.instruction:
A more step by step guide can be found [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2017/11/01/cinnamon-star-bread-bakealong)

### Prep
- Sift flour, potato flour and dry milk through a strainer

### Making The Dough
- Combine 2 cups of flour, 1/4 cup of potato flour, 1/4 cup of nonfat dry milk, between 198g to 227g of lukewarm water, 4 tablespoons of *room teperature* unsalted butter, 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract, 2 teaspoons of instant yeast, 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of salt
- Knead by hand or machine (with dough hook) till is its soft and smooth
- Place in lightly greased bowl and let rise for 60 minutes or until it doubled in bulk

### Shaping
- Divide the dough into 4 equal pieces
- Shape each piece into a ball
- Cover balls and allow them to rest for 15 minutes
- On a lightly greased or floured work surface, roll one piece of dough into a 10 inch circle
- Place the circle on a piece of parchment paper and brush a thin coat of beaten egg on the surface, then evenly cover with 1/3 of the cinnamon-sugar leaving 1/4 inch of bare dough around the perimeter
- Roll out a second circle the same size and place it on top of the filling covered circle
- Repeat the layering process - egg, cinnamon sugar, dough circle - leaving the top circle bare
- Place a 2.5 inch to 3 inch round cutter in the center of the dough circle as a guide. With a bench knife or a sharp knife cut the circle into 16 equal strips from the center to the edge, through all the layers
- Using two hands, pick up two adjacent strips and twist them away from each other twice to the top side is facing up again.
- Repeat wit the remaining strips of dough so that you end up with 8 pairs of strips
- Pinch the pairs of strips together to create a star-like shape with the points 
- Remove cutter
- Transfer the star on the parchment paper to a baking sheet. 
- Cover and let rest for about 45 minutes

### Baking
- Preheat your oven for 400F
- Brush the star with a thin coat of beaten egg
- Bake for 12 to 15 minutes
- Let cool for about 10 minutes
